Buddhists unfurl a 25-year-old, 196-foot-long sacred Thangka painting during Wesak day or Buddha Day festival celebrations at the Enlightened Heart Tibetan Buddhist temple in Ipoh, outside Kuala Lumpur in Malaysia on Sunday. Wesak commemorates the birth of Buddha, his attaining enlightenment and his death on the full moon of May, which fell on Saturday this year. Photo: AFP Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star